@node "wotsit" "What is it?"

  @{b}@{fg shine}@{bg fill}Sufferer@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back}

  Sufferer is a file suffix renamer.

  It allows the mass-renaming of file extensions, so if
  you've got a load of JPEG files with a .jpeg extension,
  you can change the .jpeg to .jpg for example. Or you
  could turn loads of .txt files into .readme files, for
  the sake of continuity, and so on...

  IMPORTANT NOTE! See the Icon section of @{"Usage" link "usage" 0}!
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

  @{b}Usage@{ub}

  Just run it from WB or CLI (there are no CLI parameters - it
  only uses a reqtools requester).

  Just select the files whose suffixes you want to change, using
  the reqtools multi-select requester. Enter a pattern into the
  pattern gadget (eg #?.iff) to make your selection easier if you
  want.

  Note that, for conservation of memory reasons, you can only select
  1000 files at a time, good enough for most people, but not so
  good for animation freaks I guess. If anyone needs more, either modify
  the supplied Blitz source, or contact me to compile a bigger version.

  Then just enter a new extension for your files (it doesn't matter
  if you supply the "." or not, as the program will check for you).

  @{fg shine}IMPORTANT!@{fg text} - There's a bug in one of the Blitz commands,which means
  that if you cancel the suffix requester, or enter an empty string,
  you get an Enforcer hit. To avoid this, type Abort (set up by default)
  and click OK if you decide to cancel the renaming process. Sorry!

  @{b}Icons@{ub}

  By default, the file requester only shows your files. If your files
  have icons attached, you must click on the [.info] gadget in the file
  requester to be able to select the icons as well!
@endnode

